the college of health and human sciences has a tradition of academic excellence that has been made possible by the financial gifts of support from alumni, parents and friends.these contributions provide funding to meet new and exciting programmatic needs in the college, or one of the departments, schools or program within the college. your donation provides assistance for student scholarships and addresses emerging needs.outright gifts provide the college with much needed financial assistance. they have an immediate impact on students, faculty and programs.at times, the college accepts "gifts in kind" in the form of equipment, supplies, materials, software or hardware. please contact dean audrey shillington or sonia wright to discuss such gift ideas.many businesses and corporations match personal gifts to educational institutions made by employees, retirees, and their family members. please contact your company's personnel office for more information.all gifts are tax deductible. if you want to donate to the college of health and human sciences and its programs, please visit theuniversity givingpage or complete and mail thedonation form [pdf], along with your check to:college of health and human sciencessan jose state universityone washington squaresan jose, ca 95192-0049(408) 924-2900for more detailed information on a specific fund or scholarship, or to establish a new scholarship or award, please contact sonia wright:sonia r. wright, cfre, cspgsr. director of developmentdirect: 408-924-1328cell/text: 530-340-2278sonia.wright@sjsu.edudean's office phone:408-924-2900fax:408-924-2901email:health-human-sciences@sjsu.edugive to the chhs fundsign up for our chhs newsletter